        <type><ref refid="structagc__state__t" kindref="compound">agc_state_t</ref> *</type>
        <definition>agc_state_t * agc_create</definition>
        <argsstring>(double ref_db, double loop_bw, double alpha)</argsstring>
        <name>agc_create</name>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>ref_db</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>loop_bw</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>alpha</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Create an AGC instance. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ref_db</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Target output power in dB (e.g. 0.0). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>loop_bw</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Loop noise bandwidth, normalised (cycles/sample); ~1/(4*loop_bw) samples to settle. Smaller is slower and smoother. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>alpha</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Power-detector EMA coefficient in (0, 1]. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Heap-allocated state, or NULL on allocation failure. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para><computeroutput>gain_db</computeroutput> starts at 0 dB (unity gain); <computeroutput>p_avg</computeroutput> is seeded with the reference power 10^(ref_db/10) so the loop starts settled. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Caller must call <ref refid="agc__core_8h_1a27364c1a1ed4be8879c624ba34e7537b" kindref="member">agc_destroy()</ref> when done. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
